    <title>Creating and Starting Threads</title>

    <para>Creating and starting new threads of execution is indeed very simple in Java.
        The complexities of multi threaded coding, however, become pertinent when multiple
        threads share common resources.
    </para>
    <note>
        <para>
            Though a low-level understanding of Threads is useful, it is recommended that
            the Java Concurrency Utilities (<literal>java.util.concurrent</literal>),
            introduced with Java 5, be used for all multi-threading use-cases due to the
            greater safety, simplicity, and power.

        </para>
    </note>

